{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4d5946b3-e80c-4986-82fe-e934fbcea67a","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01JDr6ydvQJnLSJM2oWtkpxo","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Migrating xUnit v2 to v3"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01Fomg3Vd9qaWoS6fH3zNHpu","name":"bash","arguments":{"command":"cd /tmp/sv-2b3c7a7e161a46fbb67353f83a900bca && dotnet package search xunit.v3 --exact-match --take 1 2>/dev/null | head -20","description":"Search for latest xunit.v3 package version","initial_wait":15},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"Search for latest xunit.v3 package version"}],"interactionId":"4cfdd76b-bd15-4c8a-8d4f-243e78652299","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I understand the full picture. Let me migrate from xUnit v2 to xUnit v3:\n\n1. **Directory.Packages.props**: Replace `xunit` (v2 meta-package) with `xunit.v3` and remove `xunit.runner.visualstudio` (not needed in v3) and `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` (not needed in v3).\n\n2. **TestProject.csproj**: \n   - Replace `xunit` with `xunit.v3`\n   - Remove `xunit.runner.visualstudio` and `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`\n   - Change the project to an executable using `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` with `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` or switch to the xUnit runner SDK.\n\n3. **BasicTests.cs**: The `using Xunit;` namespace and test attributes like `[Fact]` and assertions like `Assert.Equal` remain unchanged in v3.\n\n4. **global.json**: xUnit v3 uses `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` as its test runner instead of VSTest.\n\nFor the migration, I need to swap out the `xunit` package for `xunit.v3`, remove `xunit.runner.visualstudio` and `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` since they're no longer required, and configure the project as an executable with `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` and `<GenerateProgramFile>false</GenerateProgramFile>`.\n\nNow I'm checking what the latest stable version of `xunit.v3` actually is—it should be somewhere in the 1.0.x range based on current releases.","outputTokens"